&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/tom_martin/"&gt;Tom_Martin2010&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/tom_martin/5123862646/" title="Victoria falls in the dry season"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm2.static.flickr.com/1397/5123862646_7de9f4139a_m.jpg" width="240" height="130" alt="Victoria falls in the dry season" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;An old, fairly rubbish picture of Victoria Falls. Taken with an old film camera from the Zambian side of the falls.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/tom_martin/"&gt;Tom_Martin2010&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/tom_martin/5136545550/" title="Victoria falls- wet season"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4131/5136545550_173de3d89d_m.jpg" width="240" height="167" alt="Victoria falls- wet season" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Another old film picture of Victoria Falls on the Zamiba/Zimbabwe border, this time taken at the end of the wet season&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/7272097@N08/"&gt;NettyA on holidays&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/7272097@N08/5188954016/" title="Crossing the Zambezi, 1975"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm2.static.flickr.com/1005/5188954016_3e4bd60114_m.jpg" width="240" height="116" alt="Crossing the Zambezi, 1975" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In 1975, this was the only way to travel from Rhodesia (now Zimbabwe) to Zambia, crossing the Zambezi on a ferry to Botswana. This was the overland truck I travelled in.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/mikomiao/"&gt;mikomiao&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/mikomiao/5198469294/" title="~290~ gorgeous"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4125/5198469294_7e2b3376a8_m.jpg" width="240" height="159" alt="~290~ gorgeous" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The view from the waiting area for the high wire activities is amazing and I'm so glad I brought my wide angle with me. Even though there is no water here (it might be our timing as we went nearest the time of lowest water volume) the rock formations are gorgeous and so untouched. &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Our &lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/mikomiao/5197756643"&gt;zipline&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/mikomiao/5197750781/"&gt;platform&lt;/a&gt; and the gorge swing platform are to the left of the shot just out of view, but you can see the cable for the gorge swing (you bungee jump off the platform on a rop that's attached to the middle of a cable strung across the gorge) across the cliff. &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
In the distance is the Victoria Falls Bridge which connects Zimbabwe and Zambia over the Zambezi river. We crossed the border on foot later on the trip and walked across the bridge. &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
YIP 2010&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/rickinzim/"&gt;rickinzim&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/rickinzim/5203307621/" title="&amp;quot;The Life....&amp;quot;"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4132/5203307621_3da900b19c_m.jpg" width="240" height="180" alt="&amp;quot;The Life....&amp;quot;" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sundowners on a sand bank on the Zambezi river. Life can't get any better !&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/dfid/"&gt;DFID - UK Department for International Development&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/dfid/5217140149/" title="Bringing water to the crops thanks to an irrigation project"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5248/5217140149_bbb474a986_m.jpg" width="240" height="159" alt="Bringing water to the crops thanks to an irrigation project" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;An irrigation project in Mozambique, run by Save the Children with UKaid support from the British government, has enabled women like Falesse to grow onions and tomatoes, which they can now sell in large quantities at the market. The income helps them to provide for their children and improve their living conditions.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Photo &amp;copy; Marcos Villalta / Save the Children&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
For more information and to watch a film about the project, please visit: &lt;a href="http://www.dfid.gov.uk/zambezi" rel="nofollow"&gt;www.dfid.gov.uk/zambezi&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/dfid/"&gt;DFID - UK Department for International Development&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/dfid/5217140151/" title="Falesse Joaquim (left)"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5288/5217140151_7c5d95e416_m.jpg" width="240" height="159" alt="Falesse Joaquim (left)" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Falesse (left) is the treasurer of an association which produces vegetables with an irrigation system.  “We want to have an activity that doesn’t depend so much on the weather and with irrigation we can basically produce all year round.”&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Photo: Marcos Villalta / Save the Children&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
For more information and to watch a film: &lt;a href="http://www.dfid.gov.uk/zambezi" rel="nofollow"&gt;www.dfid.gov.uk/zambezi&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/dfid/"&gt;DFID - UK Department for International Development&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/dfid/5217140157/" title="Onions growing in an irrigated field"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5003/5217140157_b6b9755c6a_m.jpg" width="240" height="159" alt="Onions growing in an irrigated field" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To stop crops being washed away unexpectedly, the Floodplain Management Project is providing subsistence farmers in the Zambezi Valley with new ways of irrigating crops and helping them to plant in less flood-prone areas.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Photo: Marcos Villalta / Save the Children&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
For more information and to watch a film: &lt;a href="http://www.dfid.gov.uk/zambezi" rel="nofollow"&gt;www.dfid.gov.uk/zambezi&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/dfid/"&gt;DFID - UK Department for International Development&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/dfid/5217140161/" title="Rosa tends her goats"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4089/5217140161_ea609ecb2a_m.jpg" width="240" height="159" alt="Rosa tends her goats" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;“The goats are very resistant and thrive here, whether there is a drought or floods. I already have two baby goats although we only started a few months ago. I’m going to have more and more goats and sell some of them.”&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Photo: Marcos Villalta / Save the Children&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
For more information and to watch a film: &lt;a href="http://www.dfid.gov.uk/zambezi" rel="nofollow"&gt;www.dfid.gov.uk/zambezi&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/dfid/"&gt;DFID - UK Department for International Development&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/dfid/5217140167/" title="Looking to the future with goats"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5282/5217140167_82972159bb_m.jpg" width="240" height="159" alt="Looking to the future with goats" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With support from Save the Children and funded by the British government’s Department for International Development, each association member received five goats.  The Floodplain Management Project aims to create livelihoods which are environmentally and economically viable.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Photo: Marcos Villalta / Save the Children&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
For more information and to watch a film: &lt;a href="http://www.dfid.gov.uk/zambezi" rel="nofollow"&gt;www.dfid.gov.uk/zambezi&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/dfid/"&gt;DFID - UK Department for International Development&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/dfid/5217140171/" title="Rosa in a battle of wills"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5010/5217140171_53a905e367_m.jpg" width="240" height="159" alt="Rosa in a battle of wills" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;“This year, we sowed our seeds, then there was a flood which washed everything away.  We planted again and another flood came so we lost everything.” So Rosa and her fellow villagers formed an association and decided to diversify into goat-raising.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Photo: Marcos Villalta / Save the Children&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
For more information and to watch a film: &lt;a href="http://www.dfid.gov.uk/zambezi" rel="nofollow"&gt;www.dfid.gov.uk/zambezi&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/dfid/"&gt;DFID - UK Department for International Development&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/dfid/5217711188/" title="Isobel and her fellow bakers"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5209/5217711188_37074099b2_m.jpg" width="240" height="159" alt="Isobel and her fellow bakers" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In just two hours today, Isobel’s association has already sold half of its bread.  “My dream is that we reach a point where we can overcome all the challenges that we’ve had with the drought and the floods so we don’t have to worry about whether we are going to have enough food or not” says Isobel.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Photo: Marcos Villalta / Save the Children&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
For more information and to watch a film: &lt;a href="http://www.dfid.gov.uk/zambezi" rel="nofollow"&gt;www.dfid.gov.uk/zambezi&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/dfid/"&gt;DFID - UK Department for International Development&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/dfid/5217711208/" title="Isabel Joaquim Marquez (left)"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5164/5217711208_6868207264_m.jpg" width="240" height="159" alt="Isabel Joaquim Marquez (left)" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Isabel: “When I was a young girl there was always a good harvest that we could rely on.  What we now get from the fields is much lower.  But with the sale of bread, we’ve managed to generate some income.”&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Photo: Marcos Villalta / Save the Children&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
For more information and to watch a film: &lt;a href="http://www.dfid.gov.uk/zambezi" rel="nofollow"&gt;www.dfid.gov.uk/zambezi&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/dfid/"&gt;DFID - UK Department for International Development&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/dfid/5217711212/" title="Bread going into the oven"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5165/5217711212_aa01c510a8_m.jpg" width="240" height="159" alt="Bread going into the oven" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Funds from the British government via Save the Children helped Isabel Joaquim Marquez and her partners to build this oven and learn how to bake bread.  Baking provides the group with an alternative source of income when harvests fail.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Photo: Marcos Villalta / Save the Children&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
For more information and to watch a film: &lt;a href="http://www.dfid.gov.uk/zambezi" rel="nofollow"&gt;www.dfid.gov.uk/zambezi&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/dfid/"&gt;DFID - UK Department for International Development&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/dfid/5217711224/" title="Preparing the dough"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4131/5217711224_1e67b0f63e_m.jpg" width="240" height="159" alt="Preparing the dough" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With recurring droughts and floods, producing food is a major issue.  But setting up a bakery with funding from Britain has meant that one association is managing to generate income to buy food and clothes for their families.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Photo: Marcos Villalta / Save the Children&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
For more information and to watch a film: &lt;a href="http://www.dfid.gov.uk/zambezi" rel="nofollow"&gt;www.dfid.gov.uk/zambezi&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/dfid/"&gt;DFID - UK Department for International Development&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/dfid/5217711230/" title="Oliveira Jose Zeca with ox cart"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4088/5217711230_1a4cc852be_m.jpg" width="240" height="159" alt="Oliveira Jose Zeca with ox cart" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Extra income comes from renting out their cart, and transporting food and goods for other people. Association member Oliveira Jose Zeca says: “with this additional income we will be able to pay for school fees and transport for children to access higher education.”&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Photo: Marcos Villalta / Save the Children&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
For more information and to watch a film: &lt;a href="http://www.dfid.gov.uk/zambezi" rel="nofollow"&gt;www.dfid.gov.uk/zambezi&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/dfid/"&gt;DFID - UK Department for International Development&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/dfid/5217711240/" title="Ploughing with an ox"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4127/5217711240_9f1e0780f8_m.jpg" width="240" height="159" alt="Ploughing with an ox" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Oxen are helping members of another association to expand their livelihoods.  With training, equipment and cattle from Save the Children, they have increased their planting area and moved away from the floodplains up to the highlands.  This gives them a bigger and better harvest.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Photo: Marcos Villalta / Save the Children&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
For more information and to watch a film: &lt;a href="http://www.dfid.gov.uk/zambezi" rel="nofollow"&gt;www.dfid.gov.uk/zambezi&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/people/dfid/"&gt;DFID - UK Department for International Development&lt;/a&gt; posted a photo:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/dfid/5217739762/" title="Rosa Aniva with one of her new arrivals"&gt;&lt;img src="http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5050/5217739762_5033ee9a69_m.jpg" width="240" height="159" alt="Rosa Aniva with one of her new arrivals" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This baby goat represents Rosa Aniva’s new sustainable livelihood.  Erratic rains, floods and droughts in the Zambezi River floodplains of Mozambique, mean that subsistence farmers like her can no longer rely on a harvest, so they are having to find new sources of income.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
But thanks to a climate change adaptation project run by Save the Children with support from the UK government, women like Rosa are being helped to develop alternative, sustainable means of making a living.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Photo: Marcos Villalta / Save the Children&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
